# 🎭 Deepfake Video Detection System

A Deep Learning based web application that detects whether an uploaded video is REAL or FAKE using TensorFlow, OpenCV, and Streamlit.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project analyzes uploaded videos by extracting frames and passing them through a trained Deep Learning model.

The system predicts whether the video is:

✅ REAL VIDEO

⚠️ FAKE VIDEO

along with a confidence score.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Upload video files (.mp4, .avi, .mov)
- Automatic frame extraction
- Deep Learning based classification
- Real-time prediction
- Confidence score display
- Interactive Streamlit dashboard
- User-friendly interface

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- TensorFlow / Keras
- OpenCV
- NumPy
- Streamlit

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```text
Deepfake-Video-Detection/
│
├── app.py
├── deepfake_model.h5
├── project.ipynb
├── requirements.txt
├── dataset/
│   ├── videos_real/
│   └── videos_fake/
│
└── README.md
```

---

## 📊 Dataset

The dataset contains real and fake videos used for training and testing the model.

Videos are processed by:

- Extracting frames
- Resizing frames
- Normalizing pixel values
- Feeding them into the trained model

---

## ⚙️ Installation

Install the required libraries:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## ▶️ Run Application

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 🧠 Model Workflow

1. Upload Video
2. Extract Frames
3. Preprocess Frames
4. Run Deep Learning Model
5. Predict REAL or FAKE
6. Display Confidence Score

